Aside escape Characters
If we want to place a character that is ALREADY a keyword or **reserved character** we use the back slash(/) 

## Strike Through
We can use strike through characters or words using tilde (~)
e.g
Mr. Ubial knows how to spell ~~neighbour~~

## BlockQuotes 
Block quotes allow us to emphasize a bigger chunk of text
We use carpts (>) to create Block Quotes

eg
>This is an example of a blockquote 
  Sasdasfsdfadf
# Lists
We can create both *unordered* and *ordered* lists
## Unordered lists
To create each point, we use asteriks (/*)  with a space behind it
e.g
* egg
* Dairy 
* cheese 
* milk
For sub bullets press tab before the asteriks

## Ordered lists
If there is a specific order to the elements in our list, we can create an ordered list We use numbers, followed by periods to create ordered lists

e.g 

1. Put butter into mixing bowl
2. Add sugar to butter (Hold shift then enter to add a second line)
   Specifically brown sugar and granulated sugar 
3. Mix sugar with butter with mixing bowl

# Tables 
We can organize information in tables using Markdown
We use dashes (-) and pipes (|)

Tables in Mardown require HEADINGs

e.g 

| Name   |Age   |Sign   |
| --- |  --- | --- |
| Burce Wayne | 35 | Aquarius|
